---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
	title="FAQ"
	description="Frequently asked questions about Sonia Buddy bus timetables and vehicle rental services in West Bengal."
>
	<section class="hero">
		<div class="container">
			<h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
			<p>Find answers to common questions about our services</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section>
		<div class="container">
			<div class="section-title">
				<h2>General Questions</h2>
			</div>

			<div class="faq-item">
				<h3>What is Sonia Buddy?</h3>
				<p>Sonia Buddy is a West Bengal travel service platform that provides bus timetable information and vehicle rental services. We help travelers find bus schedules and connect with vehicle rental providers including cars, buses, toto, pickup vans, and ambulances with drivers.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="faq-item">
				<h3>Is Sonia Buddy free to use?</h3>
				<p>Yes, searching for bus timetables and vehicle rental information on Sonia Buddy is completely free. We do not charge any fees for accessing basic information on our platform.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="faq-item">
				<h3>Which cities in West Bengal do you cover?</h3>
				<p>We currently cover major cities including Kolkata, Siliguri, Durgapur, Asansol, Burdwan, Darjeeling, and are continuously expanding our coverage to more locations across West Bengal.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="section-title mt-3">
				<h2>Bus Search Questions</h2>
			</div>

			<div class="faq-item">
				<h3>How do I search for bus timetables?</h3>
				<p>Visit our Bus Search page, enter your departure city (From) and destination city (To), and click the Search button. Our system will display available bus schedules and timings for your route.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="faq-item">
				<h3>What information is available in bus timetables?</h3>
				<p>Our bus timetables include departure times, arrival times, bus types (AC, Non-AC, Sleeper, Seater), route information, and contact details for bus operators where available.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="faq-item">
				<h3>Can I book bus tickets through Sonia Buddy?</h3>
				<p>Currently, we provide timetable information to help you plan your journey. Ticket booking features are being developed and will be available soon.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="section-title mt-3">
				<h2>Vehicle Rental Questions</h2>
			</div>

			<div class="faq-item">
				<h3>What types of vehicles can I rent?</h3>
				<p>We offer various vehicle types including cars (sedans, SUVs), buses (mini buses and full-size buses), toto (three-wheelers), pickup vans, ambulances, and tempo travellers.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="faq-item">
				<h3>Do rental vehicles come with drivers?</h3>
				<p>Yes, all vehicle rentals listed on Sonia Buddy come with professional drivers. We ensure that drivers are experienced and licensed.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="faq-item">
				<h3>How do I book a rental vehicle?</h3>
				<p>Search for vehicles by city and type on our Rent Vehicle page. Once you find a suitable option, you can contact the vehicle owner directly through the provided contact information to discuss details and make arrangements.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="faq-item">
				<h3>What are the rental charges?</h3>
				<p>Rental charges vary based on vehicle type, distance, duration, and other factors. Each vehicle listing provides pricing information, and you can discuss specific rates directly with the vehicle owner.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="section-title mt-3">
				<h2>Support Questions</h2>
			</div>

			<div class="faq-item">
				<h3>How can I contact Sonia Buddy?</h3>
				<p>You can reach us through our Contact page. We typically respond to inquiries within 24-48 hours.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="faq-item">
				<h3>What if I find incorrect information?</h3>
				<p>We strive to keep our information accurate and up-to-date. If you find any incorrect information, please contact us immediately so we can verify and correct it.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="card mt-3">
				<h3>Still have questions?</h3>
				<p>If you couldn't find the answer to your question, please feel free to <a href="/contact">contact us</a> directly.</p>
				<a href="/contact" class="btn">Contact Us</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>
